race.comment: LONE ARTIST (4) was well found when resuming at the Sunny Coast but just ran into a couple better on that occasion. Will have come on with that run now under the belt and where there's smoke there's fire. Can improve enough to take this out. HEESEN (3) was a touch disappointing in Sydney when resuming but will find this assignment much easier. Gets 3kg off with the claim and must be respected from the Freedman barn. Looms as the main danger. The well-related ANARITA (5) (full to G2 winner Kristilli) will be ready to peak now third-up from the spell and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. In the mix. SOUTHERN MONEY (6) is a former Victorian having her first run for the new stable. Keep safe. GOLD FEVER (2) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be underestimated.
